Path:   Inventory Management > Transfer Stock  section  > Send Stock   If admin want to send stock from his warehouse to another warehouse, he can use this feature to record stock sending.   The process to Send stock is:  Add new send stock > Prepare Product list > Select Products > Start Send Stock > Save Receive Stock > Mark as Completed   Step 1: Add new send stock      (1) Fill the  Transfer Code    (2) Choose  Source Warehouse    (3) Choose  Destination Warehouse  (4) Fill in the  Reason  box   Step 2: Prepare the product list      To prepare product list, click on the  Prepare Product List  button   Here you have 3 options to prepare products to be sent:
--   Scan barcode : if you have our barcode management module installed;
--   Select Products : from the full list of your inventory;
--   Import : via a CSV file (with a provided sample).  If you choose Select Products:   (1) Click on the product needed  (2) Then, click on  Add Selected Products  button   (3) Choose the quantity to transfer and click on  Start Send Stock  (4) You can click on  Remove  to delete product line   The system will dislpay a notification when the transfer is completed.   Step 3: Receive stock:  Destination warehouse can create receives by either  importing  via a CSV file or  selecting products  from the list of Sent products.    If you click on  Select Products  in  Receiving history  tab:   (1) Select the product to receive   (2) Click on  Add Selected Products   Enter the quantity received in receiving history   Click on  Save Receive  and the system will display a notification about the Successful Receipt   You can also view and download the  Shortfall List  – the list containing the products that the Destination warehouse does not receive from Source warehouse:   Or  Return products , also on the same page:

Path:   Inventory Management > Transfer Stock  section  > Request Stock   If a warehouse lacks of stock, admin can create a Stock request to get stock from other warehouse. The process to request stock is:  Add new request stock > Prepare Product list > Select Products> Start Request Stock > Save Delivery Stock > Save Receive Stock > Mark as Completed   Step 1: Add new request stock      (1) Fill the  Transfer Code    (2) Choose  Source Warehouse    (3) Choose  Destination Warehouse  (4) Fill in the  Reason  box   Step 2: Prepare the product list      To prepare product list, click on the  Prepare Product List  button   Here you have 3 options to prepare products to be sent:
--   Scan barcode : if you have our barcode management module installed;
--   Select Products : from the full list of your inventory;
--   Import : via a CSV file (with a provided sample).  If you choose Select Products:   (1) Click on the product needed  (2) Then, click on  Add Selected Products  button   (3) Enter the quantity to transfer   (4) Click on  Start Request Stock  *  You can click on  Remove  to delete product line   The system will dislpay a notification when the transfer is completed.   Step 3: Delivery History:  Source warehouse when receives the stock request can create a stock delivery. When a stock delivery is created, stock will be subtracted immediately from the source warehouse.    You can either import products via a CSV file or click on  Select Products  in delivery history.  If you choose to Select Products   (1) Select the products to added  (2) Click on  Add Selected Products   Enter the quantity received in delivery history àn click on  Save Delivety   Step 4: Receive History:  Destination warehouse can create receives by importing or selecting product then update received qty.     Click on  Select Products  in receiving history   (1) Select the products to receive  (2) Click on  Add Selected Products   Enter the quantity received in receiving history and click on  Save Receive .   The system will display a message when the receiving is created successfully.   After that, stock will be added immediately to the destination warehouse from which the stock request was sent.  You can also download  Shortfall List & Summary  of the Stock Request.

To create/ edit purchase orders, manage deliveries from suppliers to warehouses and return items from warehouses to suppliers, go to  Purchase Management > Purchase Order > Purchase Order . The Manage Purchase Orders page contains information related to all POs including  Reference Number, Date of the PO, Supplier, Ordered Qty, Received Qty, Billed Qty, Total Paid, Grand Total inclusive Tax  (i.e. the total value of the PO) and  Status .    There are 3 types of Status indicating to which stage the PO has been processed:
-  Pending : when you have input General Information and prepared product list;
-  Processing : when you click the Confirm Purchase Order button;
-  Completed : when you click the Complete PO button.  Click on view a PO to see more details of the PO and you can continue editing the PO.

a. Send stock to another internal warehouse  Path:  Inventory Management > Transfer Stock  section  > Send Stock  If admin wants to send stock from his warehouse to another warehouse, he can use this feature to record stock sending.   The process to Send stock is:  Add new send stock > Prepare Product list > Select Products > Start Send Stock > Save Receive Stock > Mark as Completed   Step 1: Add new send stock     Fill the  Transfer Code  Choose  Source Warehouse    Choose  Destination Warehouse   Fill in the  Reason  box    Step 2: Prepare the product list:     To prepare product list, click on the  Prepare Product List  button   Here you have 3 options to prepare products to be sent:
-  Scan barcode : if you have our barcode management module installed;
-  Select Products : from the full list of your inventory;
-  Import : via a CSV file (with a provided sample).  If you choose Select Products:    Click on the product needed  Then, click on  Add Selected Products  button     Choose the quantity to transfer and click on  Start Send Stock  You can click on  Remove  to delete product line    The system will dislpay a notification when the transfer is completed.   Step 3: Receive stock:  Destination warehouse can create receives by either  importing  via a CSV file or  selecting products  from the list of Sent products.    If you click on  Select Products  in  Receiving history  tab:    Select the product to receive   Click on  Add Selected Products    Enter the quantity received in receiving history   Click on  Save Receive  and the system will display a notification about the Successful Receipt:   You can also view and download the  Shortfall List  – the list containing the products that the Destination warehouse does not receive from Source warehouse:   Or  Return products , also on the same page:    b. Request Stock  Path:  Inventory Management > Transfer Stock  section  > Request Stock  If a warehouse lacks stock, admin can create a Stock request to get stock from other warehouse. The process to request stock is:  Add new request stock > Prepare Product list > Select Products> Start Request Stock > Save Delivery Stock > Save Receive Stock > Mark as Completed   Step 1: Add new request stock:       Fill the  Transfer Code  Choose  Source Warehouse    Choose  Destination Warehouse   Fill in the  Reason  box    Step 2: Prepare the product list:     To prepare product list, click on the  Prepare Product List  button   Here you have 3 options to prepare products to be requested:
    -  Scan barcode:  if you have our barcode management module installed;
    -  Select Products:  from the full list of your inventory;
    -  Import : via a CSV file (with a provided sample).  If you choose Select Products:    Click on the product needed  Then, click on  Add Selected Products     Enter the quantity to transfer   Click on  Start Request Stock   You can click on  Remove  to delete product line   The system will dislpay a notification when the transfer is completed.   Step 3: Delivery History : Source warehouse when receives the stock request can create a stock delivery. When a stock delivery is created, stock will be subtracted immediately from the source warehouse.    You can either import products via a CSV file or click on  Select Products  in delivery history.  If you choose to Select Products:    Select the products to be added  Click on  Add Selected Products    Enter the delivered quantity in delivery history and click on  Save Delivery   Step 4: Receive History : Destination warehouse can create receives by importing or selecting product then update received qty.     Click on  Select Products  in receiving history    Select the products to receive  Click on  Add Selected Products    Enter the quantity received in receiving history and click on  Save Receive.   The system will display a message when the receiving is created successfully.   After that, stock will be added immediately to the destination warehouse from which the stock request was sent.  You can also download  Shortfall List & Summary  of the Stock Request.
